<div class="heading"><%= @title %></div>

<div class="question">
	How can I sign up and add my restaurant to Forkfile?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	To add your restaurant to Forkfile, please <b><%= link_to "contact us", :controller => "notification", :action => "restaurantOwners" %></b>.
	
	We will request information from you, including your restaurant information and menu. Once we receive all
	necessary information, we will begin the process of adding your menu to Forkfile. When that is complete,
	we will notify you and enable your account to receive orders.
</div>


<div class="question">
	How will my customers find out?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	As the restaurant owner, you know best how to advertise to your customers. Therefore, you are 
	responsible for informing your customer's of your new online ordering service. Several options 
	we suggest include the following:
	
	<ul>
		<li>Hang at least one large sign in your restaurant</li>
		<li>Link to Forkfile.com from your restaurant's website</li>
		<li>Update your menus to advertise Forkfile as a ordering option</li>
		<li>Provide Forkfile ads in delivery / take out bags</li>
	</ul>
	
</div>


<div class="question">
	My restaurant is not in any major city.  Can I join Forkfile?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Yes, all restaurants in the US may join Forkfile.
</div>



<div class="question">
	Will my menu be compatible with the Forkfile system?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Forkfile is able to incorporate almost any menu into its system. On rare occasions, very complex menu items
	may not be supported.
</div>

<div class="question">
	How do I receive an order?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Forkfile sends all orders via fax to the number you provide.
</div>

<div class="question">
	What should I do if my fax machine stops working?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Please resolve the issue as soon as possible or contact your Forkfile representative to temporarily disable your account. If any orders are faxed during this time, you will receive a confirmation phone call listing the phone number of the customer. Please follow up with the customer to complete the order.
</div>

<div class="question">
	What if an order was faxed to me but I do not notice it?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Forkfile will follow up each order with an automatic phone call to verify you received the order.
</div>

<div class="question">
	How do I cancel my account?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Please contact your Forkfile representative to cancel your account. You may cancel at any time. There is no contract.
</div>

<div class="question">
	My restaurant is closed on certain holidays. How do I prevent orders during those days?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Please inform your Forkfile representative of all days the restaurant will be closed.
</div>

<div class="question">
	One of my menu items was added incorrectly. How can I have this fixed?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Please contact your Forkfile representative and we will correct the issue. If the price was incorrect and
	orders were received for this item,	please request a refund and specify all associated order numbers.
</div>

<div class="question">
	How do customers pay the restaurant through Forkfile?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Forkfile does not accept payments from customers. It is the restaurant's responsibility to accept the payment
	from the customer. If a customer selects credit card as the method of payment, Forkfile will simply forward this
	information on to the restaurant to process.
</div>


<div class="question">
	The customer called and changed or canceled the order after submitting through Forkfile. How do I get a refund?
</div>
<div class="answer">
	Please wait until you receive a bill for this period and then contact your Forkfile representative to request a refund.
	Please specify the associated order number.
</div>

